Title: Test hygiene: test_pipeline_io leaks stray run-report files into data/catalogs/run_reports
Created: 2026-07-22
Author: HDMX-coding-agent

--- log ---
2026-07-22T12:23Z HDMX-coding-agent created

--- body ---
## Context

Surfaced during PR #1082 review (ticket 0284): the e2e suite leaked
`catalog_merge__*.json` into the real DVC-tracked `data/catalogs/run_reports/`
because `save_run_report` resolves `CATALOGS_DIR` from `pipeline_loaders` at
call time. PR #1082 fixed the leak for `tests/test_pipeline_e2e.py` (patching
`pipeline_loaders.CATALOGS_DIR` in the `_patched_merge_dirs` fixture), but
`tests/test_pipeline_io.py` has the same defect shape and four pre-existing
stray run-report files were observed in the real `run_reports/` directory.

## Actions

1. Patch `pipeline_loaders.CATALOGS_DIR` (not just the `utils` re-export) in
   `test_pipeline_io.py` fixtures, mirroring the `_patched_merge_dirs` fix.
2. Identify and remove the stray test-generated `run_reports/*.json` files
   from the primary checkout (verify they are test fixtures, not real run
   reports, before deleting — check filenames/content against known runs).
3. Sweep other test modules calling `save_run_report` for the same
   patch-the-wrong-module shape (grep-before-commit rule).

## Test

- After the fix, running the full suite leaves `data/catalogs/run_reports/`
  byte-identical to its pre-suite state.

## Exit criteria

- [ ] No test writes into the real run_reports directory
- [ ] Stray files removed (or justified and kept)
